# Testing Rules

- New business logic should include tests.
- Prefer unit tests for pure logic.
- Prefer integration/slice tests for Spring wiring.
- Avoid mocking simple value objects.
- For WebFlux endpoints, prefer WebTestClient.
- Architecture constraints should be enforced with ArchUnit tests.
- Tests should verify behavior, not implementation details.
